<TITLE> Court refuses BDR men bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 2 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court refused bail Thursday to BDR members detained in the Peelkhana carnage case. Judges rejected four to five bail appeals among the hundreds of accused produced in the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court since morning. Court pollice sub-inspector Khandaker Eklasur Rahman told bdnews24.com a total of 822 people, mainly border guards with some civilians, had been arrested so far. Of them, 780 accused were being produced in Thursday's court, he said. Of the remainder, some were in remand and others were reportedly ill. Prosecution assistant police commissioner Md Anisur Rahman told bdnews24.com all the detainees would be produced in the court by 2pm. Some 40 were the first to appear in the dock of magistrate Faisal Atiq Bin Quader at around 8:45am, . Those who were currently on remand for questioning were not produced in the court. The accused were taken to the court in 40 prison vans amid tight security cordon by police, riot police and the Rapid Action Battalion, Eklasur Rahman said. No lawyer or justice-seeker was allowed inside the court since the morning, but the restrictions were relaxed after 11:30am. bdne
